                        Quizzes
                    </div>

                    <div class="content" id=
                    "experiment-article-section-6-content">
                        <p><b>Q1.</b> Time taken for one complete oscillation
                        is called Time Period of the oscillator.<br>
                        <input id="q1" name="q1" type="radio" value="1">
                        True<br>
                        <input id="q1" name="q1" type="radio" value="0">
                        False<br>
                        <br>
                        <b>Q2.</b> Time period of the oscillator is constant
                        for given values of mass, length and initial
                        conditions.<br>
                        <input id="q2" name="q2" type="radio" value="1">
                        True<br>
                        <input id="q2" name="q2" type="radio" value="0">
                        False<br>
                        <br>
                        <b>Q3.</b> Value of Time period depends on initial
                        conditions.<br>
                        <input id="q3" name="q3" type="radio" value="1">
                        True<br>
                        <input id="q3" name="q3" type="radio" value="0">
                        False<br>
                        <br>
                        <b>Q4.</b> Value of time period depends on mass.<br>
                        <input id="q4" name="q4" type="radio" value="1">
                        True<br>
                        <input id="q4" name="q4" type="radio" value="0">
                        False<br>
                        <br>
                        <b>Q5.</b> Value of time period depends on length of
                        the oscillator.<br>
                        <input id="q5" name="q5" type="radio" value="1">
                        True<br>
                        <input id="q5" name="q5" type="radio" value="0">
                        False<br>
                        <br>
